{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "648b5a6e417cc3fb48d67cd9", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb96"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "62c481f101514d218a7934d9", "title": "JEE Main 2022 (28 Jun Shift 1)", "isVisible": true}], "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 2, "approximateTimeRequired": 120, "question": {"text": "<p><strong>Statement - I :</strong> When <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#956;</mi></math> amount of an ideal gas undergoes adiabatic change from state <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math> to state <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math>, then work done is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>&#956;</mi><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>&#947;</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub></mfrac></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo></math> universal gas constant.</p><p><strong>Statement - II :</strong> In the above case, when work is done on the gas, the temperature of the gas would rise.</p>", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "mnJbv", "text": "Both statement-I and statement-